<h1 class="page-header">Getting Started</h1>
<blockquote>
  <h3>Let's start fresh!</h3>
  <p>
    We need to make sure we all work from the same code base.
  </p>
</blockquote>

<h3>Step 1</h3>
<blockquote>
  <p>Whether you did not complete the tutorial from Rails Intermediate or if you would like to start fresh, clone the following repository:</p>

  <pre><code>git clone https://github.com/mathieugagne/milo-app.git</code></pre>

</blockquote>

<h3>Step 2</h3>
<blockquote>
  <div class="console">
    <span>Type this in the terminal:</span><pre>cd milo-app</pre>
  </div>
  <div class="message">
    <p>'cd' stands for change directory.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="message">
    <p>'cd milo-app' makes milo our current directory.</p>
  </div>
</blockquote>

<h3>Step 3</h3>
<blockquote>
  <div class="message">
    <p>Open the milo-app folder as a project in your text editor.</p>

    <p>In <strong>Sublime Text 2</strong>, you can use the <code>Project &gt; Add Folder to Project...</code> menu option:</p>

    <p><%= image_tag "sublime_add_folder_to_project.png", alt: '' %></p>
  </div>
</blockquote>